<Document>
<name>Vršič Pass</name>
<description><![CDATA[<h2>Vršič Pass</h2><p><i>Slovenia · Triglav National Park, Kranjska Gora to Bovec</i></p><p><b>50 numbered hairpins in 50 km, built by Russian POWs in WWI, climbing to 1,611 m.</b></p><table style='font-family:sans-serif'><tr><td><b>Approx. length:</b></td><td>31 km (19 mi)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Drive time:</b></td><td>1.5–2 hrs no stops; full day with</td></tr><tr><td><b>Best season:</b></td><td>Late May–October</td></tr><tr><td><b>Watch out for:</b></td><td>50 hairpins, steep gradients, often closed in winter, narrow lanes, tour buses</td></tr><tr><td><b>Track points:</b></td><td>87</td></tr></table><hr><p>50 numbered hairpins in 50 km. Built 1915–17 by Russian POWs of the Austro-Hungarians during the Soča (Isonzo) Front of WWI — one of the bloodiest fronts in human history (1.7 million casualties on a 100-km front). Many of the Russians died in a single avalanche on March 8, 1916; the wooden Russian Chapel at hairpin 8 commemorates them. The Soča River the road descends to is the most photographed in Slovenia — a surreal emerald color from limestone-filtered glacial meltwater. Hemingway drove an ambulance here in 1918 (the basis for A Farewell to Arms). The pass is the highest in Slovenia.</p><h3>Scenic points marked on this route:</h3><ul><li><b>Lake Jasna</b> — Pair of small artificial lakes reflecting Mt Prisojnik. Sculpture of the Goldhorn (Zlatorog), the mythical white chamois of Slovene legend.</li><li><b>Russian Chapel</b> — Wooden chapel at hairpin 8, built 1916 by surviving Russian POW road-builders to honor those killed. Annual Russian Orthodox memorial each summer.</li><li><b>Vršič Pass summit</b> — 1,611 m — highest pass in Slovenia. Mountain hut with food. Trail starts here for Slemenova špica peak, 1.5 hr round trip with epic Julian Alps panorama.</li><li><b>Izvir Soče</b> — Source of the Soča emerges from a rock face. 15-min walk from parking, then short scramble with steel cables to the spring itself. Water is so transparent it's invisible until you look for it.</li><li><b>Velika korita Soče</b> — Most spectacular section of the Soča Gorge — emerald water in narrow limestone slots, rope bridges, swimming holes (cold!) in summer.</li></ul><hr><p><i>Track geometry is interpolated between named waypoints — use a routing service to snap to actual road for navigation. Waypoints, scenic POIs, and notes are reliable.</i></p>]]></description>
